3.	RECOMMENDED DR STRATEGY
________________________________________
Recommended Solution:
Azure Service Bus Geo-Disaster Recovery (Geo-DR)
Geo-DR provides native metadata replication between paired Premium namespaces and significantly reduces operational overhead associated with maintaining duplicate Service Bus configurations.
Benefits
• Automatic replication of queues.
• Automatic replication of topics.
• Automatic replication of subscriptions.
• Replication of authorization rules.
• Replication of namespace metadata.
• Consistent DR configuration.
• Reduced operational effort.
• Simplified failover process.
Geo-DR does not replicate:
• Active messages.
• Scheduled messages.
• Dead-letter messages.
• In-flight transactions.
________________________________________
4.	MESSAGE REPLICATION CONSIDERATIONS
________________________________________
Message replication is not recommended for this workload.
Reasoning
The TTO platform processes documents stored within Azure Blob Storage utilizing geo-redundant storage capabilities.
Service Bus messages act primarily as processing instructions and do not represent the source system of record.
In the event of a regional outage:
• Documents remain available within secondary storage.
• Processing can be replayed.
• Applications can regenerate messages if required.
Implementing message replication would introduce:
• Additional operational complexity.
• Duplicate message handling requirements.
• Message ordering challenges.
• Increased infrastructure cost.
• Additional support burden.
Based on the current architecture, metadata replication alone is considered sufficient.
