11.	OPERATIONAL CONSIDERATIONS
________________________________________
In-Flight Messages
Geo-DR replicates metadata only.
Messages present in the primary namespace at the time of failover are not replicated to the DR namespace.
Applications should implement retry and replay mechanisms where message loss cannot be tolerated.
Dead-Letter Queues
Dead-letter queues should be reviewed before failover and after recovery.
Any required replay activity should be coordinated with application owners.
Message Ordering
Message ordering may be temporarily impacted during failover activities.
Applications requiring strict ordering should validate processing after failover.
Capacity Planning
DR namespaces should maintain equivalent Premium Messaging Unit capacity to production namespaces.
